    <item>
      <title>About Me</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am a Mechanical Engineering student at IUBAT with a resolute trajectory toward aerospace technology and a future at NASA. My journey is defined by a passion for discovery—from identifying celestial bodies to engineering innovative mechanical systems.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Current Academic Focus (6th Semester)&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;current-academic-focus-6th-semester&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#current-academic-focus-6th-semester&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Currently immersed in advanced studies at IUBAT, including:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manufacturing Processes &amp;amp; Economics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Linear Algebra &amp;amp; Electronics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Independent Research:&lt;/strong&gt; Self-studying human anatomy and physiology to explore the intersection of biomechanics and aerospace engineering.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Key Achievements&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;key-achievements&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#key-achievements&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NASA Citizen Scientist Award:&lt;/strong&gt; Discovered 3 provisional Asteroids via NASA JPL Laboratory (2019).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Presidency Gold Medal Award&lt;/strong&gt; (2019).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Science Festivals:&lt;/strong&gt; 14 Champion titles for Project Displays across Bangladesh.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Olympiads:&lt;/strong&gt; Multi-award winner in Physics and Biology Olympiads.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Leadership &amp;amp; Vision&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;leadership--vision&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#leadership--vision&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Co-Founder, H.O.L.M.E.S. Research Group:&lt;/strong&gt; Establishing a four-founder framework for cross-disciplinary mechanical research.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hult Prize Competitor:&lt;/strong&gt; Developing innovative social entrepreneurship solutions for global challenges.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>The H.O.L.M.E.S. Initiative</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/holmes-initiative/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/holmes-initiative/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Here we detail the constitutional framework and primary objectives of the four-founder H.O.L.M.E.S. research group.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Our current focus lies in bridging the gap between theoretical mechanical engineering and practical, aerospace-applicable innovation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
